						<div class="postbody">On PCE you don't need any VRAM finding routine as you can CRAM sprites in all your 64ko .<br />Personally i use a double buffer in VRAM if dynamic sprites is needed(E.G:for BTU) as you can write to it at any time.<br /><br />For OAM/SAT, no registrers is needed, as personally i write directly to VRAM .<br /><br />I think if you lack of index registers, you must use pointers, for your OAM buffer perhaps .</div>

