						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Espozo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Having under 256 different instructions must have been a bitch when designing this thing.</div><br />Try coding for the Super FX.  16 registers, 8-bit instruction size.  And lots of instructions need source, operand and destination registers.  Something as simple as XOR requires a prefix instruction just to specify the operation because they ran out of opcodes.<br /><br />But yeah, it's a tad limiting.  Just upgrading the 65xx concept to 16-bit without worrying about backward compatibility would have resulted in a massively more powerful processor.  I kinda like the idea of a Z register too...</div>

